Define a predicate $\beta_k$ on formal power series by
$$\beta_k F := \qquad F = (x + k) + zF^2 + zF + 2z^2 {\partial \over \partial z}F$$
By finitely unrolling it out to whichever power of $z$ we're
interested in, we can see for each $k$ there is a unique power series
$F$ that satisfies $\beta_k F$. Call it $M_k$.

Now we want to show for all k that
$$M_k = (x+k)[z M_{k+1}]$$
Here I'm using the list constructor $[F]$ to stand for the
geometric series $1 / (1 - F)$.

By universal property, it suffices to show $\beta_k((x+k)[z M_{k+1}])$. I'm going to make some abbreviations
