\subsection{$z$-derivative of $M^k$}
Recall that $[z]_z = [z]^2$ and so $[F]_z = F_z [F]^2$.

So if $M^k = (x+k)[z M^{k+1}]$, then
$$M^k_z = (x+k)[z M^{k+1}]_z$$
$$ = (x+k)(z M^{k+1})_z[z M^{k+1}]^2$$
$$ = (x+k)(M^{k+1} + z M_z^{k+1})[z M^{k+1}]^2$$

